// Regression: SAME-ARITY twin-fieldset closure fields. The nullable arm
// `{a: {f: i64}, f: (i32, i32, i32) => K0, z: f32}` and the a-closure's RESULT row
// `{a: i32[], f: (i32, i32, i32) => string, z: K1}` both spell the fieldset {a, f, z},
// so `fieldClosureFeOfRecv` aliased the narrowed `t0.f(1, 1, 1)` call onto the OTHER
// row's lambda — `cloCallSigKey`'s arity guard cannot split same-arity twins, and the
// `ref.cast` took a struct-result functype: a runtime TRAP (fuzz post-#991 branching
// leg, seed 142348133 case_00233). Fixed twice over: (1) `cloCallSigKey` verifies the
// syntactic resolve against the CHECKER-typed callee (a divergent `annSigKey` means
// the twin aliased — the typed key drives the cast); (2) `exprString`'s member-callee
// arm gates its string claim on `!nodeTyIsLitUnionAlias` (the K0 atom result reps i32
